    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-10T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="870"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12791.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-10T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1914, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 9, 6 p.m. Am gratified to learn prospect good for entry of
                    Constitutionalists without bloodshed. Do everything in your power to assist
                    peaceful transfer. While this Government’s influence will be exerted with the
                    Constitutionalists to prevent harshness and cruelty it will be exerted on the
                    side of the Federals to secure compliance with the plans imposed by the
                    Constitutionalists. In this way we can render to both sides the best service
                    that the conditions permit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
